main event: Sighting of an object presumed to be a satellite on 17 May 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed for a brief period of ten seconds., The sighting lasted a total of 24 seconds with a second sighting occurring 1 1/2 hours later., The object was described as appearing similar to a falling star of second magnitude., The report involved multiple sources, including military and naval entities., There is no photograph included in the report despite a section mentioning photos.
sighted object: an object presumed to be a satellite
witness description: Military personnel aboard the USS Savage
